President Trump gave remarks at Joint Base Andrews in Maryland, stating that progress is being made with North Korea. He mentioned that Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has had positive meetings and will be meeting again. Kim Jong Un is expected to deliver a letter to President Trump, which he looks forward to receiving. The President also mentioned that the economy is doing well, with the stock market up and low unemployment rates. He will be visiting Dallas and Houston later that day. When asked about the content of the letter and whether a deal is taking shape, President Trump expressed optimism but emphasized that it is a process and that he wants any meeting to be meaningful.